<br>
Blender is difficult to learn, but it works and is free. Once you DO learn it, it is pretty awesome.<br>
<br>
You can find dozens of tutorials though, www.blendermania.com have a few. I used to have the big list with all of the tutorials on it (around 30-40) that you can use to teach yourself.<br>
<br>
I'm still learning too. I've posted a few pictures I've made so far with blender at <!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://clubs.yahoo.com/clubs/lookandlearnhow2drawanime">clubs.yahoo.com/clubs/loo...2drawanime</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
in the pictures section under &quot;Tempests terrible art&quot;.<br>
You might have to join to see them though (when your done you can un-join if you wish)<br>
<br>
There is actually a reference manual online thats free, but not the entire detailed one. It just teaches you basics.<br>
